From −20 °C to 100 °C, an increase in the dark current through the device can be seen in Fig. 2; this could be due to the greater thermal energy available at higher temperatures, changes in series resistance could also contribute to the observed increase. The observed dependence between dark current and the applied forward bias followed the expected relationship for a simple p-n diode; such relationship is summarised in equation 2.2I=I0exp{qV/nkT}\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
